    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A chamber designed to create a vacuum environment by removal of air and gasses with a pump. In conservation science practice, vacuum chambers are used for such purposes as drying, degassing, fumigation, resin impregnation. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
